Patch Set 12: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

The ibh_mr_shift test breaks everything again. How can you test ibh_mr_size before you call ib_querydevice() which sets ibh_mr_size for the first time? If you want the test you need to place it after the following code:

if (hdev->ibh_mr_size == ~0ULL) {
                hdev->ibh_mr_shift = 64;
                return 0;
        }
}

As it stands this patch completely breaks ko2iblnd.
